Package com.here.android.mpa.venuemaps Description

Note: Venuemaps package has been deprecated in preference for the 3D Venue features delivered in the com.here.android.mpa.venues3d package. Please see the venues3d package introduction for more details and usage instructions.

The venuemaps package provides classes, interfaces, and enumerations related to venue maps. A venue map provides details of the interior of a building, including information such as the structure of each floor and room names. The starting point of this package is the VenueMaps class.

Venue maps are set to visible through Map.setVenueMapTilesVisible(boolean).

To use this feature, your application must include the google-gson library (release 2.2.4 or a compatible version) on its class path. This library can be downloaded from the google-gson project website at http://code.google.com/p/google-gson/. Attempting to use this feature without adding this library will cause runtime errors.

For more information on using venue maps, please consult the "Venue Maps" section in the HERE SDK for Android Developer's Guide.
